over 45 really however healers etc can get away with being a little lower.  Good fire/mag resists are required too, to avoid being feared/DD'd with fire.<br>
<br>
Naggy is needed for the bard and war epic (red scale) and perhaps more.  Ragefire is required for the cleric epic.  As I understand it, Zordilak Ragefire the merchant spawns up to 18 hours after Naggy is dead.   The cleric then gives him something and Ragefire spawns.  Naggy has a lev 52 soft ceiling, meaning that if you are 53 or more and attack him you get shunted from the zone.  You can however seem to get away with heals (at least for a while, until you get on his agro list).  Mages can CoH and all buffers can of course buff.<br>
<br>
Ragefire has no level cap.<br>
<br>
My plan is to have the cleric that needs Ragefire camp his spot until he spawns.  To keep it simple it would be good if a CoH mage could bind there as well, to enable easy assembly.<br>
<br>
